<dashboard version="1.1" theme="dark" stylesheet="css/sit-core.css,css/sit-components.css">
  <label>Best Practices</label>
  <description>Tips and guidelines for building great Splunk dashboards</description>

  <row>
    <panel>
      <html>
        <div class="sit-scope" style="padding: 30px; text-align: center;">
          <h1 style="font-size: 32px; margin-bottom: 16px;">Best Practices Guide</h1>
          <p style="font-size: 18px; color: #A0A0A0; max-width: 700px; margin: 0 auto;">
            Follow these guidelines to build maintainable, performant, and user-friendly Splunk dashboards.
          </p>
        </div>
      </html>
    </panel>
  </row>

  <row>
    <panel>
      <title>1. Always Use the sit-scope Class</title>
      <html>
        <div class="sit-scope" style="padding: 20px;">
          <div style="display: flex; gap: 20px; flex-wrap: wrap;">
            <div style="flex: 1; min-width: 300px;">
              <h4 style="color: #DC3545; margin-bottom: 12px;">Bad</h4>
              <div style="background: rgba(220, 53, 69, 0.1); border-radius: 8px; padding: 16px; font-family: monospace; font-size: 13px;">
                <pre style="margin: 0; color: #A0A0A0;"><code>&lt;html&gt;
  &lt;button class="sit-btn"&gt;
    Button
  &lt;/button&gt;
&lt;/html&gt;</code></pre>
              </div>
              <p class="sit-text-muted" style="margin-top: 12px; font-size: 13px;">Styles may conflict with Splunk's default styles.</p>
            </div>

            <div style="flex: 1; min-width: 300px;">
              <h4 style="color: #5CC05C; margin-bottom: 12px;">Good</h4>
              <div style="background: rgba(92, 192, 92, 0.1); border-radius: 8px; padding: 16px; font-family: monospace; font-size: 13px;">
                <pre style="margin: 0; color: #A0A0A0;"><code>&lt;html&gt;
  <span style="color: #5CC05C;">&lt;div class="sit-scope"&gt;</span>
    &lt;button class="sit-btn"&gt;
      Button
    &lt;/button&gt;
  <span style="color: #5CC05C;">&lt;/div&gt;</span>
&lt;/html&gt;</code></pre>
              </div>
              <p class="sit-text-muted" style="margin-top: 12px; font-size: 13px;">Scoped styles prevent conflicts.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </html>
    </panel>
  </row>

  <row>
    <panel>
      <title>2. Use Semantic Button Variants</title>
      <html>
        <div class="sit-scope" style="padding: 20px;">
          <p style="margin-bottom: 16px;">Choose button variants based on their meaning, not just appearance:</p>

          <div class="sit-table-wrapper">
            <table class="sit-table sit-table-striped">
              <thead>
                <tr>
                  <th>Variant</th>
                  <th>When to Use</th>
                  <th>Example</th>
                </tr>
              </thead>
              <tbody>
                <tr>
                  <td><span class="sit-badge sit-badge-primary">Primary</span></td>
                  <td>Main action on the page (1 per section max)</td>
                  <td>Save, Submit, Create</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td><span class="sit-badge" style="background: var(--sit-secondary); color: white;">Secondary</span></td>
                  <td>Alternative actions</td>
                  <td>Cancel, Back, Reset</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td><span class="sit-badge sit-badge-success">Success</span></td>
                  <td>Positive/confirm actions</td>
                  <td>Approve, Enable, Confirm</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td><span class="sit-badge sit-badge-error">Danger</span></td>
                  <td>Destructive actions</td>
                  <td>Delete, Remove, Disable</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td><span class="sit-badge" style="background: transparent; border: 1px solid var(--sit-primary); color: var(--sit-primary);">Outline</span></td>
                  <td>Less prominent actions</td>
                  <td>Learn More, View Details</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td><span class="sit-badge" style="background: transparent; color: var(--sit-text-secondary);">Ghost</span></td>
                  <td>Minimal emphasis, toolbars</td>
                  <td>Icon buttons, menu items</td>
                </tr>
              </tbody>
            </table>
          </div>
        </div>
      </html>
    </panel>
  </row>

  <row>
    <panel>
      <title>3. Provide User Feedback</title>
      <html>
        <div class="sit-scope" style="padding: 20px;">
          <p style="margin-bottom: 20px;">Always show feedback for user actions:</p>

          <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(300px, 1fr)); gap: 20px;">
            <div class="sit-card">
              <div class="sit-card-header"><h4 class="sit-card-title">Loading States</h4></div>
              <div class="sit-card-body">
                <p class="sit-text-secondary" style="margin-bottom: 12px;">Show spinners or loading buttons during async operations:</p>
                <button class="sit-btn sit-btn-primary sit-btn-loading">Saving...</button>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="sit-card">
              <div class="sit-card-header"><h4 class="sit-card-title">Toast Notifications</h4></div>
              <div class="sit-card-body">
                <p class="sit-text-secondary" style="margin-bottom: 12px;">Confirm successful actions with toast messages:</p>
                <code class="sit-code">SITToast.success('Saved!')</code>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="sit-card">
              <div class="sit-card-header"><h4 class="sit-card-title">Error Handling</h4></div>
              <div class="sit-card-body">
                <p class="sit-text-secondary" style="margin-bottom: 12px;">Show clear error messages when things fail:</p>
                <code class="sit-code">SITToast.error('Failed to save')</code>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </html>
    </panel>
  </row>

  <row>
    <panel>
      <title>4. Confirm Destructive Actions</title>
      <html>
        <div class="sit-scope" style="padding: 20px;">
          <p style="margin-bottom: 16px;">Always ask for confirmation before destructive actions like delete:</p>

          <div style="background: #1F2527; border-radius: 8px; padding: 16px; font-family: monospace; font-size: 13px; overflow-x: auto;">
            <pre style="margin: 0; color: #A0A0A0;"><code>$('#delete-btn').on('click', function() {
    <span style="color: #FD1875;">SITModal.confirm(</span>
        'Are you sure you want to delete this item? This cannot be undone.',
        'Confirm Delete',
        function() {
            // User confirmed - proceed with delete
            performDelete();
        },
        function() {
            // User cancelled
        }
    <span style="color: #FD1875;">)</span>;
});</code></pre>
          </div>

          <div style="margin-top: 16px; padding: 12px; background: rgba(247, 181, 0, 0.1); border-left: 4px solid #F7B500; border-radius: 4px;">
            <strong style="color: #F7B500;">Tip:</strong> <span class="sit-text-secondary">Use the danger button variant in confirm dialogs for destructive actions.</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </html>
    </panel>
  </row>

  <row>
    <panel>
      <title>5. Keep Forms Simple</title>
      <html>
        <div class="sit-scope" style="padding: 20px;">
          <div style="display: flex; gap: 30px; flex-wrap: wrap;">
            <div style="flex: 1; min-width: 300px;">
              <h4 style="margin-bottom: 16px;">Form Guidelines</h4>
              <ul style="color: var(--sit-text-secondary); line-height: 2;">
                <li>Mark required fields with <code class="sit-code">sit-label-required</code></li>
                <li>Add helper text for complex fields</li>
                <li>Show validation errors inline</li>
                <li>Disable submit button until form is valid</li>
                <li>Group related fields together</li>
              </ul>
            </div>

            <div style="flex: 1; min-width: 300px;">
              <h4 style="margin-bottom: 16px;">Example</h4>
              <div class="sit-form-group">
                <label class="sit-label sit-label-required">Email Address</label>
                <input type="email" class="sit-input sit-input-error" value="invalid-email" />
                <span class="sit-error-text">Please enter a valid email address</span>
              </div>
              <div class="sit-form-group">
                <label class="sit-label">API Key</label>
                <input type="password" class="sit-input" placeholder="Enter your API key" />
                <span class="sit-help-text">Find your API key in Settings</span>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </html>
    </panel>
  </row>

  <row>
    <panel>
      <title>6. Use Consistent Spacing</title>
      <html>
        <div class="sit-scope" style="padding: 20px;">
          <p style="margin-bottom: 16px;">Use CSS variables for consistent spacing throughout your dashboard:</p>

          <div class="sit-table-wrapper" style="margin-bottom: 20px;">
            <table class="sit-table sit-table-striped">
              <thead>
                <tr>
                  <th>Variable</th>
                  <th>Value</th>
                  <th>Use For</th>
                </tr>
              </thead>
              <tbody>
                <tr><td><code class="sit-code">--sit-spacing-xs</code></td><td>4px</td><td>Tight spacing (icon gaps)</td></tr>
                <tr><td><code class="sit-code">--sit-spacing-sm</code></td><td>8px</td><td>Small gaps (button groups)</td></tr>
                <tr><td><code class="sit-code">--sit-spacing-md</code></td><td>16px</td><td>Default spacing (form groups)</td></tr>
                <tr><td><code class="sit-code">--sit-spacing-lg</code></td><td>24px</td><td>Section padding</td></tr>
                <tr><td><code class="sit-code">--sit-spacing-xl</code></td><td>32px</td><td>Large section gaps</td></tr>
              </tbody>
            </table>
          </div>

          <div style="background: #1F2527; border-radius: 8px; padding: 16px; font-family: monospace; font-size: 13px;">
            <code style="color: #A0A0A0;">&lt;div style="padding: var(--sit-spacing-lg); gap: var(--sit-spacing-md);"&gt;</code>
          </div>
        </div>
      </html>
    </panel>
  </row>

  <row>
    <panel>
      <title>7. Accessibility Tips</title>
      <html>
        <div class="sit-scope" style="padding: 20px;">
          <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(280px, 1fr)); gap: 16px;">
            <div style="padding: 16px; background: var(--sit-bg-dark); border-radius: 8px;">
              <h4 style="margin-bottom: 8px;">Keyboard Navigation</h4>
              <p class="sit-text-secondary sit-text-sm">All interactive elements should be keyboard accessible. Test with Tab key.</p>
            </div>

            <div style="padding: 16px; background: var(--sit-bg-dark); border-radius: 8px;">
              <h4 style="margin-bottom: 8px;">Color Contrast</h4>
              <p class="sit-text-secondary sit-text-sm">Don't rely on color alone to convey information. Use text labels and icons.</p>
            </div>

            <div style="padding: 16px; background: var(--sit-bg-dark); border-radius: 8px;">
              <h4 style="margin-bottom: 8px;">Focus States</h4>
              <p class="sit-text-secondary sit-text-sm">The toolkit provides visible focus states. Don't disable them.</p>
            </div>

            <div style="padding: 16px; background: var(--sit-bg-dark); border-radius: 8px;">
              <h4 style="margin-bottom: 8px;">Labels</h4>
              <p class="sit-text-secondary sit-text-sm">Always associate labels with form inputs for screen readers.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </html>
    </panel>
  </row>

  <row>
    <panel>
      <html>
        <div class="sit-scope" style="padding: 20px; text-align: center;">
          <div style="padding: 20px; background: rgba(92, 192, 92, 0.1); border-radius: 8px; display: inline-block;">
            <h3 style="color: #5CC05C; margin-bottom: 8px;">You're Ready!</h3>
            <p class="sit-text-secondary">Follow these practices and you'll build great dashboards.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </html>
    </panel>
  </row>

</dashboard>
